['text':' This is a implementation of per directory history for zsh, some','line_number':3,'multiline':False]
['text':' implementations of which exist in bash[1,2].  It also implements','line_number':4,'multiline':False]
['text':' a per-directory-history-toggle-history function to change from using the','line_number':5,'multiline':False]
['text':' directory history to using the global history.  In both cases the history is','line_number':6,'multiline':False]
['text':' always saved to both the global history and the directory history, so the','line_number':7,'multiline':False]
['text':' toggle state will not effect the saved histories.  Being able to switch','line_number':8,'multiline':False]
['text':' between global and directory histories on the fly is a novel feature as far','line_number':9,'multiline':False]
['text':' as I am aware.','line_number':10,'multiline':False]
